mixin magic_item_table(bonuses, costs, notes)
  table.magic_items
    thead
      tr
        each b in bonuses
          if b > 0
            th.magic_items_bonus +#{b}
          else if b < 0
            th -#{b}
          else
            th #{b}
    tbody
      tr
        each c in costs
          td.magic_items_cost #{c} gp
        if notes
          td!= notes

mixin magic_item_table_vertical(bonuses, costs, notes, header)
  table.magic_items
    if header
      thead
        tr
          th Bonus
          th Cost
          th Notes
    tbody
      each b, i in bonuses
        tr
          if b > 0
            td.magic_items_bonus +#{b}
          else if b < 0
            td -#{b}
          else
            td #{b}
          td.magic_items_cost #{costs[i]} gp
          td.magic_items_note!= notes[i]

h1 Strength

h1 Bonuses / modifiers

p Strength provides a modifier to the following actions:
  ul
    li <a href='/combat/base'>Base attack bonus</a> for melee weapons
    li <a href='/combat/damage'>Damage rolls</a> with melee or thrown weapons
    li <a href='http://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/climb'>Climb skill</a>
    li <a href='http://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/swim'>Swim skill</a>
    li <a href='/combat/maneuvers'>Combat Maneuvers</a>

h1 Improving your Strength

p There are several avenues for improving this ability. The abilities within a category do not stack. You cannot have two enhancement bonuses active at once, only the largest bonus takes effect.

p In general, magical items are the easiest way to start boosting your stats.

p Note that every two points of ability improvement provides a one point modifier to the relevant abilities listed above.

h2 Racial bonuses

p The following races receive racial bonsues to their strength.

ul
  li <a href="http://www.d20pfsrd.com/races/core-races/human">Human</a>, <a href="http://www.d20pfsrd.com/races/core-races/half-elf">Half-elf</a>, <a href="http://www.d20pfsrd.com/races/core-races/half-orc">Half-orc</a> (<i>must pick this bonus</i>)
  li <a href="http://www.d20pfsrd.com/races/3rd-party-races/adamant-entertainment/half-ogre">Half-ogre</a>

h2 Enhancment bonuses

p The following items and spells provide an enhancement bonus. Generally the highest enhancement bonus available is +6.

ul
  li <b>Spell</b>: <a href="http://www.d20pfsrd.com/magic/all-spells/b/bull-s-strength">Bull's Strength</a> (<span class="magic_items_bonus">+4</span>)
  li <b>Scroll</b>: <a href="http://www.d20pfsrd.com/magic/all-spells/b/bull-s-strength">Bull's Strength</a> scroll.
    mixin magic_item_table_vertical([4],[150],["3 min duration (<i>add 50 gp for each additional min</i>)"])
  li <b>Potion</b>: <a href="http://www.d20pfsrd.com/magic/all-spells/b/bull-s-strength">Bull's Strength</a> potion
    mixin magic_item_table_vertical([4],[300],["3 min duration (<i>add 100 gp for each additional min</i>)"])
  li <b>Wand</b>: <a href="http://www.d20pfsrd.com/magic/all-spells/b/bull-s-strength">Bull's Strength</a> wand
    mixin magic_item_table_vertical([4],[4500],["3 min duration (<i>add 1500 gp for each additional min</i>)"])
  li <b>Magical Belts</b>:
    ul
      li <a href="http://www.d20pfsrd.com/magic-items/wondrous-items/wondrous-items/a-b/belt-of-giant-strength">Belt of Giant Strength</a>
        mixin magic_item_table([2,4,6],[4000,16000,36000])
      li <a href="http://www.d20pfsrd.com/magic-items/wondrous-items/wondrous-items/a-b/belt-of-physical-might">Belt of Physical Might</a><br />This belt improves two physical stats, so two of Str, Dex AND Con.
        mixin magic_item_table([2,4,6],[10000,40000,90000])
      li <a href="http://www.d20pfsrd.com/magic-items/wondrous-items/wondrous-items/a-b/belt-of-physical-perfection">Belt of Physical Perfection</a><br />This belt improves all three physical attribute (Str, Dex AND Con).
        mixin magic_item_table([2,4,6],[16000,64000,144000])

h2 Inherent bonuses

ul
  li <a href="http://www.d20pfsrd.com/magic-items/wondrous-items/wondrous-items/a-b/book-manual-of-gainful-exercise">Manual of Gainful Exercise</a>, magical item.
    mixin magic_item_table([1,2,3,4,5],[27500,55000,82500,110000,137500])
  li <a href="http://www.d20pfsrd.com/classes/core-classes/sorcerer">Sorcerer Bloodlines</a>: some sorcerer bloodlines provide inherent bonuses to a particular stat. One example of this would be the <a href="http://www.d20pfsrd.com/classes/core-classes/sorcerer/bloodlines/bloodlines-from-paizo/abyssal-bloodline">Abyssal Bloodline</a>.


h2 Untyped bonuses

p The untyped bonus is in a category of its own and stacks with all other bonuses.

ul
  li <b>Level bonus</b><br />Every fourth level (4, 8, 12, 16, 20), the character can increase one stat by one point. <i>Note that this is only 1 point, stats typically need to be increased by two points to improve relevant abilities.</i>

